member.remarks:
On deserialization, this property has a higher priority value than ,
meaning if this property isn't , this property will be used for deserialization;
the property  won't be used; otherwise,  will be used.

Please note that type is a , which means you can use deconstruction syntax to check what key you want to check:
var (_, shiftIsDown, _, _) = Keyboard.GetModifierStateForCurrentThread();
For more information, please visit that type to learn more details.

remarks.para:
						Deconstruction methods also allow you using deconstruction patterns, like this:


if (student is (name: var name, age: >= 18))
{
    Console.WriteLine(name);
}

