member.summary:
   Looks up a localized string similar to Game over. This is your data:
Total time used: {0:hh':'mm':'ss'.'fff}
Puzzles count: {1}
Average time used: {2:hh':'mm':'ss'.'fff}
Correct rate: {3:P} ({4}/{5}).

member.remarks:
Usage:

scoped ResourceFetcher expr = $"{value:ResourceKeyName}";
string s = expr.ToString();

Here value will be inserted into the resource, whose related key value is specified as ResourceKeyName after colon token.
Its equivalent value is

string s = string.Format(ResourceDictionary.Get("ResourceKeyName", App.CurrentCulture), value);

This type is implemented via an interpolated string handler pattern, same as ,
marked with .

